At this point, the Speaker (Council Member Quinn) asked for a Moment of Silence in memory for the following individual: Army Specialist Jonathan Rivadeneira, 22, of Jackson Heights, Queens, who was killed in Iraq with 3 fellow soldiers in an IED explosion while on combat duty in Baghdad.  He was assigned to the 3rd Brigade Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Divison in Fort Hood, Texas.  During the ceremonials, Council Member Barron asked for a Moment of Silence in memory of fallen soldier Kimmel Watt.

Also, the Speaker (Council Member Quinn) asked that the Council remember the 50th anniversary of the Liitle Rock Nine attending Central High School in Little Rock, Arkansas
under Federal guard on September 25, 1957.
